  ],
  "text": "The Rust compiler's trait method resolution consists of two main phases: candidate collection and error reporting. The candidate collection phase is implemented in `compiler/rustc_trait_selection/src/traits/select/candidate_assembly.rs`, which contains the `assemble_candidates` function that collects all applicable trait method implementations for a given trait obligation. This file uses `SelectionContext` from `compiler/rustc_trait_selection/src/traits/select/mod.rs` to manage the selection process. When the candidate set is ambiguous or multiple candidates are found, the selection process (in select/mod.rs) calls into the error reporting infrastructure. The ambiguous trait method error reporting is handled in `compiler/rustc_trait_selection/src/error_reporting/traits/ambiguity.rs`, which contains the `compute_applicable_impls_for_diagnostics` function that computes applicable implementations for diagnostic purposes and the `maybe_report_ambiguity` function that generates error messages for ambiguous trait bounds. The error reporting is integrated into `compiler/rustc_trait_selection/src/error_reporting/traits/mod.rs`, which orchestrates the overall trait error reporting flow. The call chain flows from the selection process calling `assemble_candidates` to collect trait method implementations, then when multiple candidates exist or ambiguity is detected, `maybe_report_ambiguity` is invoked, which in turn calls `compute_applicable_impls_for_diagnostics` to identify and report all applicable trait implementations that caused the ambiguity."
}

